</div>
                        
                        <p><em>Lourdes rolled each tortilla up with cheese, and placed them atop chili sauce in a baking pan.&nbsp;</em></p>
<p><strong>LR: </strong>There are so many Mexicans and Hispanics in San Antonio. So the Mexican restaurants there are amazing. At home, my dad makes amazing tacos.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>TC:</strong> Do you miss Mexican food when you’re at Duke?</p>
<p><strong>LR:</strong> Yes, definitely. I eat Sazón a lot. It’s not Mexican, but it’s pretty good. They have barbacoa. In San Antonio, people eat barbacoa with Big Red.&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>TC: </strong>What’s Big Red?&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>LR:</strong> You don’t know what Big Red is? It’s a soda. Even for breakfast, people would drink it. It’s a little bit like Fanta.&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Lourdes popped the pan into the oven.&nbsp;</em></p>
<!--ceo:replacemode=raw-->




    <figure style="max-width:100%;    " class="embedded-media embedded-image">
        
        <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/1076d096-74a6-4bb5-bd4e-25286e560834.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" class="w-100" alt="" />                    <span class="embedded-credit">
                                    <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/mia-chang">Mia Chang</a>                                            </span>
                    </figure>

